    ['The Four Musketeers'] = {
        id = 10,
        start_npc = 'Any Bastok Gate Guard',
        start_zone = 'Metalworks',
        start_pos = 'J-8',
        description = 'You are to join a surprise attack on the :Category:Quadav',
        reward = 'Rank Points',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'The Emissary'},
        next = {'To the Forsaken Mines'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Trade enough Crystals (1+) to the Conquest NPC to raise your Rank bar and unlock the Mission, then accept it from the Gate Guard.\n1. Speak to Iron Eater inside the President\'s Office in Metalworks Home Point #1 at (J-8) for a cutscene.\n   - You may need to speak to him multiple times to get the cutscene.\n2. You\'ll be instructed to go to Beadeaux. Gather up a party or go solo if you are high lvl.\n   - You can teleport with the Unity Warp Lvl.122 to Pashhow Marshlands, or Survival Guide if you have it. The Survival Guide inside Beadeaux is much closer.\n3. Zone in to Beadeaux for a cutscene. You will then need to kill 20 Copper Quadavs. If you are with a party, all kills count towards the total, so you can split up to speed the process up.\n   - There are 7 Copper Quadavs in the entry area, before the tunnel, and 3 in the tunnel at the first afflictor.\n     - Using all 10 spawns makes this Mission doable in less than 8 minutes.\n   - The game will track how many you\'ve killed, and you don\'t need to kill them all at once.\n   - Be careful if you use Valaineral as your Trust, his Uriel Blade skill will AoE and most likely kill multiple Quadavs, the additional kills will not count.\n4. Upon killing 20 Copper Quadavs, zone out to Pashhow Marshlands for another cutscene. This ends the Mission.\n   - Make sure you get the cutscene with Ayame.\n   - If you do not get your 20 Copper Quadav kills, you will receive a different cutscene.\n   - If you use Escape, you will not receive the cutscene.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Pirates\' Cove'] = {
        id = 17,
        start_npc = 'Any Bastok Gate Guard',
        start_zone = 'Metalworks',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'You are being sent to Norg as an emissary of Bastok. Meet Sir Naji in front of the President\'s Office for a full briefing.',
        reward = 'Rank 7\n40,000 Gil',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'Return of the Talekeeper'},
        next = {'The Final Image'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Trade enough Crystals to the Conquest NPC to raise your Rank bar and unlock the Mission, then accept it from the Gate Guard.\n1. Speak to Naji for a cutscene.\n   - You may need to speak to him several times to get the correct cutscene.\n2. Head to Norg and speak with Gilgamesh behind the Oaken Door at (K-8). Continue speaking with him until he mentions Frag Rocks.\n   - Note: You will receive up to 6 Frag Rocks per fight.\n3. Obtain 1 Adaman Ore for every 6 players in your party/alliance.\n   - These may be obtained from the Auction House ( ➞ Materials ➞ Smithing)\n   - If none available on Auction House, they can be mined in Ifrit\'s Cauldron.  Be prepared for a long mining session as the drop is \'Very Rare\'\n4. Proceed to Yhoator Jungle (I-5) and enter Ifrit\'s Cauldron.\n   - Quick Travel options:\n   - Unity Warp (Level 122) → Yhoator Jungle → hug the right wall. It\'s a short ride.\n   - Alternatively, you may use the Elshimo Uplands Outpost Warp or Survival Guide.\n5. You will have to reach a ??? which isn\'t too far inside. You may need use Sneak and Invisible (still useful inside the Cauldron at level 99 to avoid aggroing) to get there, as there are Bats and Bombs in the way.\n6. Once inside, head left at the first intersection, and then on the next intersection go right. The ??? is in a lava flow area around (H-7), Map 1.\n7. Buff up and prepare to fight. Trading an Adaman Ore to the ??? will spawn a lvl 65 Bomb, Magma, and Salamander, a Lizard NM.\n   - Barfira is recommended.\n   - The Lizard is much weaker than the Bomb.\n   - Sneak pulling is recommended, as you only need to defeat the Bomb, and you do not need to wait for the Lizard to depop.\n   - Magma may use Self-Destruct.\n8. Upon defeating Magma, it will drop 6 Rare/Ex Frag Rocks.\n   - If doing this fight for more than 6 people, you will need to spawn them again.\n9. When everyone has their Frag Rock, head back to Norg and trade it to Gilgamesh for a cutscene.\n10. Head back to Naji for a final cutscene and your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['The Salt of the Earth'] = {
        id = 22,
        start_npc = 'Any Bastok Gate Guard',
        start_zone = 'Metalworks',
        start_pos = 'J-8',
        description = 'You have been assigned to an investigation in the Vollbow Region. Speak with senator Alois for further details.',
        reward = 'Rank Points',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'Enter the Talekeeper'},
        next = {'Where Two Paths Converge'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'Trade enough Crystals to the Conquest NPC to raise your Rank bar and unlock the Mission, then accept it from the Gate Guard.\n1. Visit Alois in the President\'s Office Conference Room in Metalworks (J-8).\n2. Head to Rabao and speak to Dancing Wolf in (G-7) for a cutscene.\n   - You may have to speak to him several times to receive the correct cutscene, make sure he mentions Miraclesalt.\n   - If he repeats the same text after talking to him several times but does not mention Miraclesalt, zone and return.  It has been observed that 3 cycles of talking and zoning has been required.\n3. Proceed to Gustav Tunnel (G-6) on Map 2, and reach the ??? located in the pond.\n   - The Unity Warp Level 128 to Gustav Tunnel places you on the correct map, just south of the pond.\n   - Alternatively, there is a Survival Guide to Map 1.\n   - Everything in the area will aggro. If in a party, you could have other players wait at (H-7), as it is safe there from aggro.\n4. Checking the ??? will spawn Gigaplasm, a slime NM.\n   - Trivial at 99 with Trusts.\n   - You can Sneak pull, sleep the NM and run back to camp. The NM will eventually make its way to you.\n   - Slime NMs have high melee resistance. Casters will be very important, and sleeping the mobs will be imperative.\n   - You will start against one Gigaplasm, defeating it will cause it to divide in 2 Macroplasms. Each of those will divide into 2 Microplasms, and those will divide into 2 Nanoplasms. Try to keep as many mobs asleep as you can. Commence by killing one line of Macroplasms (defeat one, defeat its Microplasms, and then its Nanoplasms), and then the second. Sleep repeatedly. The HP of the mobs gets progressively lower, to the point where a decently equipped BLM should be able to one-shot a Nanoplasm with a single Thunder III. The key to this fight is keeping everything asleep.\n   - Avoid giving the mobs too much TP, as they can use the typical nasty slime TP attacks, like Fluid Spread.\n5. Defeat all of them and Sneak everyone to the ???. Check it to receive the [Key Item] Miraclesalt.\n6. Return to Rabao and speak to Dancing Wolf for a cutscene.\n7. Head back to Alois to finish the Mission.',
        notes = '1. Although this Mission may prove difficult for some, it can be easily completed by two RDM/BLM, who gravity the Gigaplasm, drag it back up to the first map, and take it to the zone line.  Proceed to nuke and sleep at a distance.  If you are standing far enough away, you will not have aggro on the plasm divisions.\n2. One possible strategy from here is to have one player sleep one of the divisions, while the other casts gravity and zones the second split, causing it to deaggro and eventually depop.  If done properly and repeated each time the plasm splits, this mission becomes drastically easier.  You will still receive credit for completing the mission so long as one Nanoplasm is defeated.',
    },
